    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "left",
      "children": [
        {
          "textSize": "heading-three",
          "text": "Dancehall Reggae & The Dem Bow Beat "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "justify",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "The predominant rhythmic orientation of reggaetón is derived directly from dancehall reggae. While there is also influence from roots reggae, dancehall's textures, tempos, rapid-fire flow, and minimalist focus on 3+3+2 cross rhythms demarcated by heavy, synthesized drums have had a stronger influence. One of the most enduring features is the following "
        },
        {
          "text": "riddim ",
          "italic": true
        },
        {
          "text": "with"
        },
        {
          "italic": true,
          "text": " "
        },
        {
          "text": "a 4/4 pulse of a kick drum and syncopated snares audible in Shabba Ranks' song \"Dem Bow\" (1990). "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "justify",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "grid",
      "layout": [
        3,
        3
      ],
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "column",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": ""
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "uuid": "2d54dc74-315b-4b64-85f3-c98739d0d1b2",
